The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Fifas focus on India

Zurich: Fifa will launch a special initiative in 2007 to promote soccer in India, the games world governing body said Friday. 

India is a country with an amazing potential for growth of the beautiful game, said Fifa president Sepp Blatter, who met with Indian soccer officials in Zurich on Thursday. 

Unlike neighbour China, India have not had a major impact on world sport, and the national team is ranked 157th out of 198. China are 84th. (AP) 




